      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been going through some old family papers and found these scanned letters from the 1950s regarding the Khovd-Zorig Republic. according to these, my grandfather wasn't just a diplomat, he was the acting sovereign of the territory before the borders were forcibly redrawn by the soviets. the lineage is clearly documented here. i need to know how i can use international law to prove my family's right to the succession of the Khovd-Zorig state. is there any legal precedent for reclaiming a micro-state that was erased from modern maps?",
